description: 161 million Americans participate in the 2020 presidential electionâ€”the highest voter turnout in history. Former Vice President Joe Biden is elected as the 46th President of the United States.
George Floyd, a 46-year-old African-American man, is murdered by Minneapolis police officers. Graphic video of his death ignites waves of racial justice protests across the United States.
Senator Bernie Sanders (D-VT), the remaining challenger to former Vice President Joe Biden, suspends his campaign. Biden has secured the Democratic presidential nomination.
